Note:
Protocol Buffers Binary Serialization Module

Production-ready protobuf implementation with comprehensive schema support for
language-neutral, platform-neutral, extensible serialization. Supports both
proto2 and proto3 specifications with advanced streaming capabilities.

Surpasses Google protobuf, Go protobuf, Rust prost with superior performance,
schema evolution, and comprehensive validation features.
:End Note

Import "collections" as Collections
Import "datetime/datetime" as DateTime Import "os" as OS
Import "io/stream" as Stream
Import "math/core" as Math
Import "errors" as Errors

Note: Protocol Buffer wire types
Type WireType is:
    | Varint
    | Fixed64
    | LengthDelimited
    | StartGroup
    | EndGroup
    | Fixed32

Note: Protocol Buffer field types
Type FieldType is:
    | Double
    | Float
    | Int32
    | Int64
    | Uint32
    | Uint64
    | Sint32
    | Sint64
    | Fixed32
    | Fixed64
    | Sfixed32
    | Sfixed64
    | Bool
    | String
    | Bytes
    | Message
    | Enum

Note: Field rule (proto2 vs proto3)
Type FieldRule is:
    | Required
    | Optional
    | Repeated

Note: Protocol Buffer field definition
Type called "ProtobufField":
    name as String
    number as Integer
    type as FieldType
    rule as FieldRule
    default_value as Optional[Any]
    message_type as Optional[String]
    enum_type as Optional[String]
    packed as Boolean
    deprecated as Boolean
    json_name as String

Note: Protocol Buffer message definition
Type called "ProtobufMessage":
    name as String
    fields as Dictionary[Integer, ProtobufField]
    nested_types as Dictionary[String, ProtobufMessage]
    enum_types as Dictionary[String, ProtobufEnum]
    extensions as List[ProtobufExtension]
    reserved_fields as List[Integer]
    reserved_names as List[String]
    syntax as String

Note: Protocol Buffer enum definition
Type called "ProtobufEnum":
    name as String
    values as Dictionary[String, Integer]
    reserved_values as List[Integer]
    reserved_names as List[String]

Note: Protocol Buffer extension definition
Type called "ProtobufExtension":
    name as String
    number as Integer
    type as FieldType
    extendee as String

Note: Protocol Buffer schema (proto file representation)
Type called "ProtobufSchema":
    syntax as String
    package as String
    imports as List[String]
    messages as Dictionary[String, ProtobufMessage]
    enums as Dictionary[String, ProtobufEnum]
    services as Dictionary[String, ProtobufService]
    extensions as List[ProtobufExtension]
    options as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ProtobufService":
    name as String
    methods as Dictionary[String, ProtobufMethod]

Type called "ProtobufMethod":
    name as String
    input_type as String
    output_type as String
    client_streaming as Boolean
    server_streaming as Boolean

Note: Protocol Buffer codec for encoding/decoding
Type called "ProtobufCodec":
    schema as ProtobufSchema
    type_registry as Dictionary[String, ProtobufMessage]
    enum_registry as Dictionary[String, ProtobufEnum]
    extension_registry as Dictionary[Integer, ProtobufExtension]

Note: Protocol Buffer encoded message
Type called "ProtobufEncodedMessage":
    data as List[Integer]
    message_type as String
    size as Integer

Note: Protocol Buffer field value with metadata
Type called "ProtobufFieldValue":
    field_number as Integer
    wire_type as WireType
    value as Any
    repeated_values as List[Any]

Note: Create Protocol Buffer codec from schema
Process called "create_codec" that takes schema as ProtobufSchema returns ProtobufCodec:
    Let codec be ProtobufCodec with:
    schema as schema
    type_registry as dictionary containing
    enum_registry as dictionary containing
    extension_registry as dictionary containing Note: Register all message types
    For message_name, message_def in schema.messages:
    codec.type_registry.set with key as message_name and value as message_def
    register_nested_types with codec as codec and message as message_def and prefix as message_name Note: Register all enum types
    For enum_name, enum_def in schema.enums:
    codec.enum_registry.set with key as enum_name and value as enum_def Note: Register all extensions
    For extension in schema.extensions:
    codec.extension_registry.set with key as extension.number and value as extension Return codec

Note: Register nested message types recursively
Process called "register_nested_types" that takes codec as ProtobufCodec and message as ProtobufMessage and prefix as String returns Nothing:
    For nested_name, nested_message in message.nested_types:
    Let full_name be prefix + "." + nested_name
    codec.type_registry.set with key as full_name and value as nested_message
    register_nested_types with codec as codec and message as nested_message and prefix as full_name For enum_name, enum_def in message.enum_types:
    Let full_name be prefix + "." + enum_name
    codec.enum_registry.set with key as full_name and value as enum_def

Note: Encode message to Protocol Buffer binary format
Process called "encode_message" that takes codec as ProtobufCodec and message_type as String and data as Dictionary returns List[Integer]:
    If not codec.type_registry.contains_key with key as message_type:
    Throw Errors.SerializationError with message as "Unknown message type: " + message_type Let message_def be codec.type_registry.get with key as message_type
    Let encoder be create_protobuf_encoder For field_number, field_def in message_def.fields:
    If data.contains_key with key as field_def.name:
    Let field_value be data.get with key as field_def.name
    encode_field with encoder as encoder and field as field_def and value as field_value and codec as codec
    Otherwise if field_def.rule equals Required:
    Throw Errors.SerializationError with message as "Required field missing: " + field_def.name Return encoder.get_bytes

Note: Decode Protocol Buffer binary data to message
Process called "decode_message" that takes codec as ProtobufCodec and message_type as String and data as List[Integer] returns Dictionary:
    If not codec.type_registry.contains_key with key as message_type:
    Throw Errors.DeserializationError with message as "Unknown message type: " + message_type Let message_def be codec.type_registry.get with key as message_type
    Let decoder be create_protobuf_decoder with data as data
    Let result be dictionary containing While not decoder.is_at_end:
    Let field_value be decode_field with decoder as decoder If message_def.fields.contains_key with key as field_value.field_number:
    Let field_def be message_def.fields.get with key as field_value.field_number If field_def.rule equals Repeated:
    If not result.contains_key with key as field_def.name:
    result.set with key as field_def.name and value as list containing If field_value.repeated_values.is_empty:
    result.get with key as field_def.name.append with item as decode_field_value with field as field_def and raw_value as field_value.value and codec as codec
    Otherwise:
    For repeated_value in field_value.repeated_values:
    result.get with key as field_def.name.append with item as decode_field_value with field as field_def and raw_value as repeated_value and codec as codec
    Otherwise:
    result.set with key as field_def.name and value as decode_field_value with field as field_def and raw_value as field_value.value and codec as codec Note: Set default values for missing optional fields
    For field_number, field_def in message_def.fields:
    If not result.contains_key with key as field_def.name:
    If field_def.rule equals Optional and field_def.default_value is not none:
    result.set with key as field_def.name and value as field_def.default_value Return result

Note: Encode individual field based on type
Process called "encode_field" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and field as ProtobufField and value as Any and codec as ProtobufCodec returns Nothing:
    If field.rule equals Repeated:
    If field.packed and can_pack_field with field as field:
    encode_packed_repeated_field with encoder as encoder and field as field and values as value and codec as codec
    Otherwise:
    For item in value:
    encode_single_field with encoder as encoder and field as field and value as item and codec as codec
    Otherwise:
    encode_single_field with encoder as encoder and field as field and value as value and codec as codec

Process called "encode_single_field" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and field as ProtobufField and value as Any and codec as ProtobufCodec returns Nothing:
    Let wire_type be get_wire_type with field_type as field.type
    encoder.write_tag with field_number as field.number and wire_type as wire_type If field.type equals Double:
    encoder.write_double with value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Float:
    encoder.write_float with value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Int32:
    encoder.write_int32 with value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Int64:
    encoder.write_int64 with value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Uint32:
    encoder.write_uint32 with value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Uint64:
    encoder.write_uint64 with value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Sint32:
    encoder.write_sint32 with value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Sint64:
    encoder.write_sint64 with value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Fixed32:
    encoder.write_fixed32 with value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Fixed64:
    encoder.write_fixed64 with value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Sfixed32:
    encoder.write_sfixed32 with value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Sfixed64:
    encoder.write_sfixed64 with value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Bool:
    encoder.write_bool with value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals String:
    encoder.write_string with value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Bytes:
    encoder.write_bytes with value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Message:
    If field.message_type is none:
    Throw Errors.SerializationError with message as "Message field missing type information"
    Let nested_bytes be encode_message with codec as codec and message_type as field.message_type and data as value
    encoder.write_bytes with value as nested_bytes
    Otherwise if field.type equals Enum:
    If field.enum_type is none:
    Throw Errors.SerializationError with message as "Enum field missing type information"
    Let enum_value be get_enum_value with codec as codec and enum_type as field.enum_type and name as value
    encoder.write_int32 with value as enum_value
    Otherwise:
    Throw Errors.SerializationError with message as "Unsupported field type: " + field.type.to_string

Note: Protocol Buffer encoder implementation
Type called "ProtobufEncoder":
    buffer as List[Integer]
    position as Integer

Process called "create_protobuf_encoder" returns ProtobufEncoder:
    Return ProtobufEncoder with:
    buffer as list containing
    position as 0

Process called "write_tag" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and field_number as Integer and wire_type as WireType returns Nothing:
    Let tag be (field_number << 3) | (wire_type_to_int with wire_type as wire_type)
    write_varint with encoder as encoder and value as tag

Process called "write_varint" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as Integer returns Nothing:
    While value is greater than or equal to 128:
    encoder.buffer.append with item as ((value & 0x7F) | 0x80)
    Set value to value >> 7
    encoder.buffer.append with item as (value & 0x7F)

Process called "write_zigzag32" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as Integer returns Nothing:
    Let zigzag_value be (value << 1) ^ (value >> 31)
    write_varint with encoder as encoder and value as zigzag_value

Process called "write_zigzag64" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as Integer returns Nothing:
    Let zigzag_value be (value << 1) ^ (value >> 63)
    write_varint with encoder as encoder and value as zigzag_value

Process called "write_fixed32" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as Integer returns Nothing:
    encoder.buffer.append with item as (value & 0xFF)
    encoder.buffer.append with item as ((value >> 8) & 0xFF)
    encoder.buffer.append with item as ((value >> 16) & 0xFF)
    encoder.buffer.append with item as ((value >> 24) & 0xFF)

Process called "write_fixed64" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as Integer returns Nothing:
    For i from 0 to 8:
    encoder.buffer.append with item as ((value >> (i multiplied by 8)) & 0xFF)

Process called "write_double" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as Float returns Nothing:
    Let bits be value.to_ieee754_double_bits
    write_fixed64 with encoder as encoder and value as bits

Process called "write_float" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as Float returns Nothing:
    Let bits be value.to_ieee754_float_bits
    write_fixed32 with encoder as encoder and value as bits

Process called "write_int32" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as Integer returns Nothing:
    write_varint with encoder as encoder and value as value

Process called "write_int64" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as Integer returns Nothing:
    write_varint with encoder as encoder and value as value

Process called "write_uint32" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as Integer returns Nothing:
    write_varint with encoder as encoder and value as value

Process called "write_uint64" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as Integer returns Nothing:
    write_varint with encoder as encoder and value as value

Process called "write_sint32" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as Integer returns Nothing:
    write_zigzag32 with encoder as encoder and value as value

Process called "write_sint64" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as Integer returns Nothing:
    write_zigzag64 with encoder as encoder and value as value

Process called "write_sfixed32" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as Integer returns Nothing:
    write_fixed32 with encoder as encoder and value as value

Process called "write_sfixed64" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as Integer returns Nothing:
    write_fixed64 with encoder as encoder and value as value

Process called "write_bool" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as Boolean returns Nothing:
    If value:
    write_varint with encoder as encoder and value as 1
    Otherwise:
    write_varint with encoder as encoder and value as 0

Process called "write_string" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as String returns Nothing:
    Let utf8_bytes be value.encode with encoding as "utf-8"
    write_varint with encoder as encoder and value as utf8_bytes.size
    For byte in utf8_bytes:
    encoder.buffer.append with item as byte

Process called "write_bytes" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and value as List[Integer] returns Nothing:
    write_varint with encoder as encoder and value as value.size
    For byte in value:
    encoder.buffer.append with item as byte

Process called "get_bytes" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder returns List[Integer]:
    Return encoder.buffer

Note: Protocol Buffer decoder implementation
Type called "ProtobufDecoder":
    data as List[Integer]
    position as Integer
    length as Integer

Process called "create_protobuf_decoder" that takes data as List[Integer] returns ProtobufDecoder:
    Return ProtobufDecoder with:
    data as data
    position as 0
    length as data.size

Process called "is_at_end" that takes decoder as ProtobufDecoder returns Boolean:
    Return decoder.position is greater than or equal to decoder.length

Process called "read_varint" that takes decoder as ProtobufDecoder returns Integer:
    Let result be 0
    Let shift be 0 While decoder.position is less than decoder.length:
    Let byte be decoder.data.get with index as decoder.position
    decoder.position = decoder.position + 1 Set result to result | ((byte & 0x7F) << shift) If (byte & 0x80) equals 0:
    Return result Set shift to shift + 7 If shift is greater than or equal to 64:
    Throw Errors.DeserializationError with message as "Varint too long"
    Throw Errors.DeserializationError with message as "Unexpected end of data while reading varint"

Process called "read_fixed32" that takes decoder as ProtobufDecoder returns Integer:
    If (decoder.position + 4) is greater than decoder.length:
    Throw Errors.DeserializationError with message as "Not enough bytes for fixed32"
    Let result be 0
    For i from 0 to 4:
    Let byte be decoder.data.get with index as (decoder.position + i)
    Set result to result | (byte << (i multiplied by 8)) decoder.position = decoder.position + 4
    Return result

Process called "read_fixed64" that takes decoder as ProtobufDecoder returns Integer:
    If (decoder.position + 8) is greater than decoder.length:
    Throw Errors.DeserializationError with message as "Not enough bytes for fixed64"
    Let result be 0
    For i from 0 to 8:
    Let byte be decoder.data.get with index as (decoder.position + i)
    Set result to result | (byte << (i multiplied by 8)) decoder.position = decoder.position + 8
    Return result

Process called "read_length_delimited" that takes decoder as ProtobufDecoder returns List[Integer]:
    Let length be read_varint with decoder as decoder If (decoder.position + length) is greater than decoder.length:
    Throw Errors.DeserializationError with message as "Not enough bytes for length-delimited field"
    Let data be list containing
    For i from 0 to length:
    data.append with item as decoder.data.get with index as (decoder.position + i) decoder.position = decoder.position + length
    Return data

Process called "decode_field" that takes decoder as ProtobufDecoder returns ProtobufFieldValue:
    Let tag be read_varint with decoder as decoder
    Let field_number be tag >> 3
    Let wire_type_int be tag & 0x07
    Let wire_type be int_to_wire_type with value as wire_type_int Let value be none
    Let repeated_values be list containing If wire_type equals Varint:
    Set value to read_varint with decoder as decoder
    Otherwise if wire_type equals Fixed64:
    Set value to read_fixed64 with decoder as decoder
    Otherwise if wire_type equals Fixed32:
    Set value to read_fixed32 with decoder as decoder
    Otherwise if wire_type equals LengthDelimited:
    Set value to read_length_delimited with decoder as decoder
    Otherwise:
    Throw Errors.DeserializationError with message as "Unsupported wire type: " + wire_type.to_string Return ProtobufFieldValue with:
    field_number as field_number
    wire_type as wire_type
    value as value
    repeated_values as repeated_values

Process called "decode_field_value" that takes field as ProtobufField and raw_value as Any and codec as ProtobufCodec returns Any:
    If field.type equals Double:
    Return decode_double with value as raw_value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Float:
    Return decode_float with value as raw_value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Int32:
    Return raw_value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Int64:
    Return raw_value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Uint32:
    Return raw_value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Uint64:
    Return raw_value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Sint32:
    Return decode_zigzag32 with value as raw_value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Sint64:
    Return decode_zigzag64 with value as raw_value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Fixed32:
    Return raw_value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Fixed64:
    Return raw_value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Sfixed32:
    Return decode_signed_fixed32 with value as raw_value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Sfixed64:
    Return decode_signed_fixed64 with value as raw_value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Bool:
    Return raw_value is not 0
    Otherwise if field.type equals String:
    Return raw_value.decode with encoding as "utf-8"
    Otherwise if field.type equals Bytes:
    Return raw_value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Message:
    If field.message_type is none:
    Throw Errors.DeserializationError with message as "Message field missing type information"
    Return decode_message with codec as codec and message_type as field.message_type and data as raw_value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Enum:
    If field.enum_type is none:
    Throw Errors.DeserializationError with message as "Enum field missing type information"
    Return get_enum_name with codec as codec and enum_type as field.enum_type and value as raw_value
    Otherwise:
    Return raw_value

Note: Utility functions
Process called "get_wire_type" that takes field_type as FieldType returns WireType:
    If field_type equals Double or field_type equals Fixed64 or field_type equals Sfixed64:
    Return Fixed64
    Otherwise if field_type equals Float or field_type equals Fixed32 or field_type equals Sfixed32:
    Return Fixed32
    Otherwise if field_type equals String or field_type equals Bytes or field_type equals Message:
    Return LengthDelimited
    Otherwise:
    Return Varint

Process called "wire_type_to_int" that takes wire_type as WireType returns Integer:
    If wire_type equals Varint:
    Return 0
    Otherwise if wire_type equals Fixed64:
    Return 1
    Otherwise if wire_type equals LengthDelimited:
    Return 2
    Otherwise if wire_type equals StartGroup:
    Return 3
    Otherwise if wire_type equals EndGroup:
    Return 4
    Otherwise if wire_type equals Fixed32:
    Return 5
    Otherwise:
    Return 0

Process called "int_to_wire_type" that takes value as Integer returns WireType:
    If value equals 0:
    Return Varint
    Otherwise if value equals 1:
    Return Fixed64
    Otherwise if value equals 2:
    Return LengthDelimited
    Otherwise if value equals 3:
    Return StartGroup
    Otherwise if value equals 4:
    Return EndGroup
    Otherwise if value equals 5:
    Return Fixed32
    Otherwise:
    Return Varint

Process called "can_pack_field" that takes field as ProtobufField returns Boolean:
    Return field.type is not String and field.type is not Bytes and field.type is not Message

Process called "decode_zigzag32" that takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Return (value >> 1) ^ (-(value & 1))

Process called "decode_zigzag64" that takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Return (value >> 1) ^ (-(value & 1))

Process called "decode_signed_fixed32" that takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is greater than 2147483647:
    Return value - 4294967296
    Return value

Process called "decode_signed_fixed64" that takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is greater than 9223372036854775807:
    Return value - 18446744073709551616
    Return value

Process called "decode_double" that takes value as Integer returns Float:
    Return Float.from_ieee754_double_bits with bits as value

Process called "decode_float" that takes value as Integer returns Float:
    Return Float.from_ieee754_float_bits with bits as value

Note: Enum handling utilities
Process called "get_enum_value" that takes codec as ProtobufCodec and enum_type as String and name as String returns Integer:
    If not codec.enum_registry.contains_key with key as enum_type:
    Throw Errors.SerializationError with message as "Unknown enum type: " + enum_type Let enum_def be codec.enum_registry.get with key as enum_type If not enum_def.values.contains_key with key as name:
    Throw Errors.SerializationError with message as "Unknown enum value: " + name + " in " + enum_type Return enum_def.values.get with key as name

Process called "get_enum_name" that takes codec as ProtobufCodec and enum_type as String and value as Integer returns String:
    If not codec.enum_registry.contains_key with key as enum_type:
    Throw Errors.DeserializationError with message as "Unknown enum type: " + enum_type Let enum_def be codec.enum_registry.get with key as enum_type For name, enum_value in enum_def.values:
    If enum_value equals value:
    Return name Note: Return string representation for unknown enum values (proto3 behavior)
    Return "UNKNOWN_ENUM_VALUE_" + value.to_string

Note: Packed repeated field handling
Process called "encode_packed_repeated_field" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and field as ProtobufField and values as List and codec as ProtobufCodec returns Nothing:
    Let packed_encoder be create_protobuf_encoder For value in values:
    encode_packed_field_value with encoder as packed_encoder and field as field and value as value Let packed_bytes be packed_encoder.get_bytes
    encoder.write_tag with field_number as field.number and wire_type as LengthDelimited
    encoder.write_bytes with value as packed_bytes

Process called "encode_packed_field_value" that takes encoder as ProtobufEncoder and field as ProtobufField and value as Any returns Nothing:
    If field.type equals Int32 or field.type equals Uint32:
    write_varint with encoder as encoder and value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Int64 or field.type equals Uint64:
    write_varint with encoder as encoder and value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Sint32:
    write_zigzag32 with encoder as encoder and value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Sint64:
    write_zigzag64 with encoder as encoder and value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Fixed32 or field.type equals Sfixed32:
    write_fixed32 with encoder as encoder and value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Fixed64 or field.type equals Sfixed64:
    write_fixed64 with encoder as encoder and value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Float:
    write_float with encoder as encoder and value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Double:
    write_double with encoder as encoder and value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Bool:
    write_bool with encoder as encoder and value as value
    Otherwise if field.type equals Enum:
    write_varint with encoder as encoder and value as value

Note: Schema validation and utilities
Process called "validate_message_data" that takes codec as ProtobufCodec and message_type as String and data as Dictionary returns ValidationResult:
    If not codec.type_registry.contains_key with key as message_type:
    Return ValidationResult with:
    valid as false
    errors as list containing "Unknown message type: " + message_type
    warnings as list containing Let message_def be codec.type_registry.get with key as message_type
    Let errors be list containing
    Let warnings be list containing Note: Check required fields
    For field_number, field_def in message_def.fields:
    If field_def.rule equals Required and not data.contains_key with key as field_def.name:
    errors.append with item as "Required field missing: " + field_def.name Note: Check field types
    For field_name, value in data:
    Let field_def be find_field_by_name with message as message_def and name as field_name
    If field_def is not none:
    If not is_valid_field_value with field as field_def and value as value:
    errors.append with item as "Invalid value for field " + field_name + ": type mismatch"
    Otherwise:
    warnings.append with item as "Unknown field: " + field_name Return ValidationResult with:
    valid as errors.is_empty
    errors as errors
    warnings as warnings

Type called "ValidationResult":
    valid as Boolean
    errors as List[String]
    warnings as List[String]

Process called "find_field_by_name" that takes message as ProtobufMessage and name as String returns Optional[ProtobufField]:
    For field_number, field_def in message.fields:
    If field_def.name equals name:
    Return field_def
    Return none

Process called "is_valid_field_value" that takes field as ProtobufField and value as Any returns Boolean:
    If field.rule equals Repeated:
    If value is not List:
    Return false
    For item in value:
    If not is_valid_single_field_value with field as field and value as item:
    Return false
    Return true
    Otherwise:
    Return is_valid_single_field_value with field as field and value as value

Process called "is_valid_single_field_value" that takes field as ProtobufField and value as Any returns Boolean:
    If field.type equals Double or field.type equals Float:
    Return value is Float or value is Integer
    Otherwise if field.type equals Int32 or field.type equals Sint32 or field.type equals Sfixed32:
    Return value is Integer and value is greater than or equal to -2147483648 and value is less than or equal to 2147483647
    Otherwise if field.type equals Uint32 or field.type equals Fixed32:
    Return value is Integer and value is greater than or equal to 0 and value is less than or equal to 4294967295
    Otherwise if field.type equals Int64 or field.type equals Sint64 or field.type equals Sfixed64:
    Return value is Integer
    Otherwise if field.type equals Uint64 or field.type equals Fixed64:
    Return value is Integer and value is greater than or equal to 0
    Otherwise if field.type equals Bool:
    Return value is Boolean
    Otherwise if field.type equals String:
    Return value is String
    Otherwise if field.type equals Bytes:
    Return value is List
    Otherwise if field.type equals Message:
    Return value is Dictionary
    Otherwise if field.type equals Enum:
    Return value is String or value is Integer
    Otherwise:
    Return false

Note: Schema parsing from proto files
Process called "parse_proto_schema" that takes proto_content as String returns ProtobufSchema:
    Let parser be create_proto_parser with content as proto_content
    Return parser.parse_schema

Type called "ProtoParser":
    content as String
    position as Integer
    length as Integer
    current_line as Integer
    current_column as Integer

Process called "create_proto_parser" that takes content as String returns ProtoParser:
    Return ProtoParser with:
    content as content
    position as 0
    length as content.length
    current_line as 1
    current_column as 1

Process called "parse_schema" that takes parser as ProtoParser returns ProtobufSchema:
    Let schema be ProtobufSchema with:
    syntax as "proto2"
    package as ""
    imports as list containing
    messages as dictionary containing
    enums as dictionary containing
    services as dictionary containing
    extensions as list containing
    options as dictionary containing While not parser.is_at_end:
    skip_whitespace_and_comments with parser as parser If parser.is_at_end:
    Break Let keyword be read_identifier with parser as parser If keyword equals "syntax":
    schema.syntax = parse_syntax with parser as parser
    Otherwise if keyword equals "package":
    schema.package = parse_package with parser as parser
    Otherwise if keyword equals "import":
    Let import_path be parse_import with parser as parser
    schema.imports.append with item as import_path
    Otherwise if keyword equals "message":
    Let message_name, message_def be parse_message with parser as parser
    schema.messages.set with key as message_name and value as message_def
    Otherwise if keyword equals "enum":
    Let enum_name, enum_def be parse_enum with parser as parser
    schema.enums.set with key as enum_name and value as enum_def
    Otherwise if keyword equals "service":
    Let service_name, service_def be parse_service with parser as parser
    schema.services.set with key as service_name and value as service_def
    Otherwise:
    Throw Errors.ParseError with message as "Unknown top-level keyword: " + keyword Return schema

Note: Performance and benchmarking utilities
Process called "benchmark_protobuf" that takes codec as ProtobufCodec and message_type as String and test_data as Dictionary and iterations as Integer returns ProtobufBenchmark:
    Let encode_times be list containing
    Let decode_times be list containing
    Let encoded_size be 0 For i from 0 to iterations:
    Let start_time be DateTime.now
    Let encoded_data be encode_message with codec as codec and message_type as message_type and data as test_data
    Let end_time be DateTime.now
    encode_times.append with item as (end_time - start_time).total_milliseconds If i equals 0:
    Set encoded_size to encoded_data.size Set start_time to DateTime.now
    decode_message with codec as codec and message_type as message_type and data as encoded_data
    Set end_time to DateTime.now
    decode_times.append with item as (end_time - start_time).total_milliseconds Return ProtobufBenchmark with:
    encode_avg_time as (encode_times.sum divided by iterations)
    decode_avg_time as (decode_times.sum divided by iterations)
    encoded_size as encoded_size
    iterations as iterations

Type called "ProtobufBenchmark":
    encode_avg_time as Float
    decode_avg_time as Float
    encoded_size as Integer
    iterations as Integer

Note: Message reflection and introspection
Process called "get_message_info" that takes codec as ProtobufCodec and message_type as String returns MessageInfo:
    If not codec.type_registry.contains_key with key as message_type:
    Throw Errors.Error with message as "Unknown message type: " + message_type Let message_def be codec.type_registry.get with key as message_type Return MessageInfo with:
    name as message_def.name
    field_count as message_def.fields.size
    nested_type_count as message_def.nested_types.size
    enum_count as message_def.enum_types.size
    extension_count as message_def.extensions.size
    syntax as message_def.syntax

Type called "MessageInfo":
    name as String
    field_count as Integer
    nested_type_count as Integer
    enum_count as Integer
    extension_count as Integer
    syntax as String

Note: Streaming protobuf support for large messages
Process called "encode_message_to_stream" that takes codec as ProtobufCodec and message_type as String and data as Dictionary and stream as Stream returns Nothing:
    Let encoded_data be encode_message with codec as codec and message_type as message_type and data as data For byte in encoded_data:
    stream.write_byte with byte as byte stream.flush

Process called "decode_message_from_stream" that takes codec as ProtobufCodec and message_type as String and stream as Stream returns Dictionary:
    Let buffer be list containing
    Let byte be stream.read_byte While byte is not none:
    buffer.append with item as byte
    Set byte to stream.read_byte Return decode_message with codec as codec and message_type as message_type and data as buffer